This paper deals with the capacity of a wiretap channel with secret randomness, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the design principles of communication systems with embedded security features, which could fall under computer communications (cs.CC) and security and privacy (cs.SI). Finally, the paper investigates the concept of super-activation, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) if the transmission of large amounts of data is involved.
